definition: to wind around/to wrap round/to coil/tangle/to involve/to bother/to annoy
(of a plant) to produce (fruit or seeds)/Taiwan pr. [jie2]
knot/sturdy/bond/to tie/to bind/to check out (of a hotel)

sentences.english: Convenient cable organizer keeps cables tangle-free.
sentences.chinese: 方便的電纜電線纏結組織者保持免費。

sentences.english: Entanglement, meanwhile, is the roping together of particles in order to add more qubits.
sentences.chinese: 而纏結則是編結粒子，以此增加丘比特數。

sentences.english: The electrical wires are all twisted together.
sentences.chinese: 電線完全纏結在一起了。

sentences.english: Possible entanglement or strangulation injury when attached to crib or playpen .
sentences.chinese: 連接在童牀或遊戲圍欄時可能發生纏結或窒息危害。

sentences.english: She teased out the knots in her hair.
The CAA was often accompanied with the senile plaques and neurofibrillary tangles.
sentences.chinese: CAA往往同時伴有老年斑和神經原纖維纏結。

sentences.english: The wires are all tangled up.
Such physical entanglements are usually labile.
sentences.chinese: 這種物理纏結往往是不穩定的。
長髮容易纏結在一塊兒。

sentences.english: She combed the snarls out of her hair.
sentences.chinese: 我不知道我的頭髮爲什麼容易纏結。

sentences.english: Jewelry should not be stored together since it can be scratched or tangled.
sentences.chinese: 首飾不能保存在一起，否則易被劃傷或纏結在一起。

sentences.english: A tangled kelp forest fills the water column off the coast of Maine.
sentences.chinese: 纏結的海帶森林瀰漫着水柱沿海海面的緬因州。

sentences.english: Dislocation pile-up and tangling around carbide particles were also observed after high degree of deformation.
sentences.chinese: 變形量大時在碳化物粒子周圍形成位錯塞積和纏結。
